This code will create an image with three rectangles, each filled with the color specified by the hexadecimal code.

If you want to extract hexadecimal color codes from an existing image, you'll need to use image processing techniques to analyze the pixels of the image and convert their RGB values to hexadecimal. You can achieve this using libraries like PIL or OpenCV.

