.\path\to\your\venv\Scripts\activate    # For Windows
Replace /path/to/your/venv with the path to your virtual environment directory. Once activated, you can run pip install Pillow to install Pillow within the virtual environment.

After installation, you can verify if Pillow is installed correctly by importing it in a Python script or in the Python interpreter:

python
Copy code
import PIL
